{{Quote|Prince Aemon, the Dragonknight, may be the most famous Kingsguard who ever lived. How did he die? Defending Aegon the Unworthy from the brothers of a man who Aegon fed to his dogs. The man's crime? Sleeping with one of the many mistresses Aegon wasn't using. And the man was one of Aegon's own Kingsguard.|[[Bronn]]|The Kingsguard  (Histories &amp; Lore)}}
'''Terrence Toyne''' is an unseen character in ''[[Game of Thrones (TV series)|Game of Thrones]]''. He is long dead before the start of the series, and thus is not expected to appear. Terrence Toyne was a renowned [[knight]] of [[House Toyne]] and member of the [[Kingsguard]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Ser Terrence Toyne was fed to the dogs of King [[Aegon IV Targaryen]] for sleeping with [[Bethany Bracken|one]] of his mistresses.&lt;ref&gt;[[The Kingsguard (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Terrence Toyne is mentioned within the entry of [[Aemon Targaryen (Dragonknight)|Aemon the Dragonknight]] in the ''[[The Book of Brothers]]''. It is said that he was defeated by the Targaryen prince in the final joust in a tourney at [[Riverrun]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
